args:
Having witnessed the now-dead Ranzal speak
with Elisanne the night prior, Amane casts a
suspicious eye upon her. But that night, she is
attacked! Is Scylla disguised as Elisanne?!
Who could it be this time...?
Amane, was that you? What happened?!
Damn it all, I can't take this anymore!
Where you do think you're going, Patia?!
To find and destroy Scylla, that's where!
And how are you going to do that\nwhen she is right here among us?
Maybe the reason you're making all this\nfuss is because YOU'RE Scylla!
Me? You think I killed everyone?
If you are truly Patia, then no.\nBut I don't know if that is the case.
And I don't know if you are really Amane.
Come on, everyone, calm down.\nWe need to keep cool heads.
He's right! This is a time to stick together\nlike glue, not break apart like...not-glue.
We need each other more than ever now.
...Alas, poor Ranzal. Still, I suppose this\nmeans I can be released now?
You clearly weren't involved, so I don't\nsee a reason to keep you locked up.
In fact, Norwin is now the very FURTHEST\nperson from suspicion.
Indeed, for he is the only one of us\nwho could not have done the deed.
We should probably stick together from\nnow on. If one of us is Scylla, it's going\nto be best for us to not be separated.
So we can keep mutual eyes\non each other, you mean?
Something like that. It's not very nice,\nbut I suppose there's little point in trying\nto pretty things up at this point.
Still, we'll never get through this\nif we don't all work together.
Er, if I may, did I hear you say something\nabout one of us BEING Scylla?
...I see. So Scylla may be among us\neven as we speak.
Right, which is why we need a way\nto suss her out of hiding.
The simplest method would be to ask a \nperson a question that they—and they\nalone—would know the answer to.
We thought of that as well, and spent all\nlast night asking each other questions.

Clearly your efforts were for naught, or we
would not be having this conversation.
I suppose Scylla must have anticipated
that particular tactic.
By the way, how exactly IS Scylla\nkilling everyone?

Luca and Cleo both lacked external
wounds, and there were no signs of
a struggle about their persons.
Was this the same for Ranzal?
Then we can conclude they were all killed\nwithout offering even token resistance.
Luca and Cleo could have been surprised,\nbut Ranzal knew that Scylla is among us.\nIt would not be easy to catch him unaware.
Right... I can't imagine someone\nkilling Ranzal without him even\ntrying to fight back.
It's strange, yes, but Scylla is a fiend.\nThere may be methods available to her\nthat cannot be foreseen by us.

Yes, that possibility also exists. However,
I am not convinced that is all there is to it.
The idea she can simply kill us without
any resistance is dubious.
And yet, that is clearly what's happening,\nwhich means it's not dubious at all, no?
I think I understand what Norwin\nis trying to say.

If Scylla actually had the power to kill us
with a thought, why is she doing it day by
day and one by one instead of simply
destroying us all in one fell swoop?
Interesting. Perhaps whatever this power\nof hers is doesn't extend that far.
Or perhaps it is bound by certain rules.
Carmen called this a game, did she not?\nAnd games have rules.
Now that you mention that, I suppose\nthat nasty pig...bear...thing...whatever\nshe is! Never mind! She said it!
If there ARE rules, we need to figure out\nwhat they are, and do it fast.
Perhaps we can learn more if we find\nmore notes from old participants.
Good idea, Sinoa. Let's focus today's\ninvestigation on the private homes\nleft over on the island.
*sigh* A whole day of searching,\nand still nothing.
It's getting dark, but I REALLY\ndon't wanna sleep tonight.
We've lost one person per night so far.\nI would like to end that cycle here,\nyet have little faith we can do so.
Then we need to DO something instead\nof standing around wringing our hands!
Perhaps we could set a watch.
Indeed, if we take turns sleeping in\nsequence, it means someone is always\nawake to keep an eye on things.
Then we should split into groups—\nthree people remain awake while\nall the others sleep.
In that case, I will pair with Elisanne.\nI care not who our third is.
You seem very quick to decide that,\nAmane. Care to share why?
I'm the one who saw Elisanne\nwith Ranzal last night.
I didn't hear what they were saying,\nbut they had the look of two people\nwho were arguing with one another.
N-no! I was merely talking to him about\nthe situation we all find ourselves in!
Then why were the two of you alone?\nShouldn't the rest of us have been involved\nwith a discussion like that?
Guys, this is SO weird. Can we please stop\nwith the doubting each other already?
Yes, because that is exactly\nwhat Scylla wants us to do!
Even so, it doesn't mean we can\nsimply throw caution to the wind.
If you wish to keep an eye on me, Amane,\nyou are welcome. I have naught to hide.
Is it necessary to stare at me so?\nDo you truly find me so untrustworthy?
No, it was all just an excuse.\nI don't actually distrust you.
I know what you're planning, Elisanne:\nI know you want {player_name}\nto be the one who survives.
You heard my discussion with Ranzal!
No, but I imagined that to be the sort of\nthing you'd come up with.
And while I understand why you would\nwant the prince to escape if only one can,\nyou are being too hasty.
On the contrary, I think it's a good thing.\nIf you were Scylla, you wouldn't have\nthought to say something like that.
I think I can trust you now.
And I trust you in return, Amane.
You came to that decision quickly.\nDid it not occur to you that I might be\nlying in an attempt to trick you?
...Because I am the one tricking YOU.
Because you are in my web, little one.\nStruggle all you wish; it will not help.
You poor, stupid girl. If you hadn't trusted\nsomeone else like this, you might have\nlived a little while longer...
Do try to make your soul tasty for me, now!\nAaaaaah ha ha ha ha ha!
